2006-08-02 Wednesday 11:00  Rocky Bernstein

	* lib/driver/gnu_linux.c: Yet another guess at what happened to the
	  CDROMREADTOCENTRY ioctl call.  I haven't been able to find
	  anything that documents in any detail how to use this ioctl let
	  alone the weird behavior where CDROMREADTOC header beforehand
	  turns and "invalid parameter" into a valid one. It's not the way
	  other 'nix's work.

