2005-05-09 Monday 23:19  Rocky Bernstein

	* lib/driver/FreeBSD/freebsd.c: Heiner reports that FreeBSD's
	  passopen() and xptopen() don't allow nonblocking access so
	  O_NONBLOCK might do harm. But it's just a guess pending what
	  others discover/report.

