	* doc/: .cvsignore, version.texi: Even though this file is
	  automatically generated, CVS for the automake project seems to
	  have this checked into CVS presumably to handle the problem of a
	  missing version.texi for on initial checkout/bootstrap.

	  Seems odd, but I'm assuming automake developers know what they
	  are doing.

