	  audio sectors. ioctl READRAW doesn't always word and is slow.

2005-01-23 Sunday 14:05  Rocky Bernstein

	* lib/: cdda_interface/interface.c, paranoia/paranoia.c: Work
	  around problem where we were accessing outside of an allocate
	  range when the drive endian was different than the CD-ROM
	  endianness. We do this by always allocating an extra block, but
	  it would be better to understand whether this is correct or
	  whether some logic needs to be fixed.

